      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Plea for Help On Regional Planning</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marjorie B Serotoff letter holds Long Island is in serious need of regional planning (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Long Island section publishes numerous articles about different real estate development proposals. One recent article was about a plan to build a power plant, another about a proposed shopping mall. The common theme s the concern of neighbors about how the proposed development will affect traffic, health or quality of life.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Long Island section publishes numerous articles about different real estate development proposals. One recent article was about a plan to build a power plant, another about a proposed shopping mall. The common theme s the concern of neighbors about how the proposed development will affect traffic, health or quality of life.</p>
        <p>It appears to me that Long Island is in serious need of some regional  planning. Instead of this helter-skelter building, there must be some way for our local governments to put together proposals so that we can determine effective use of land and optimal use of resources without destroying a wonderful place to raise a family. We owe this to our children.</p>
        <p>MARJORIE B. SEROTOFF  Commack</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
